                        "prose": "This requirement has been eliminated."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a2",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Careful Allocation Of Ids",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A2"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a2"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a2_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) Each login name, each user ID (UID) and each group ID (GID) MUST ONLY be used once.\n(2) Every user MUST be a member of at least one group. (3) Every GID mentioned in the /etc/passwd\nfile MUST be defined in the /etc/group file. (4) Every group SHOULD only contain the users that\nare absolutely necessary. (5) In networked systems, care MUST also be taken to ensure that user\nand group names (UIDs and GIDs) are assigned consistently in the system network if there is a\npossibility that the same UIDs or GIDs could be assigned to different user or group names on\nthe systems during cross-system access."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a3",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "No Automatic Integration Of Removable Drives",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A3"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a3"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a3_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) Removable media such as USB pen drives or CDs/DVDs MUST NOT be integrated automatically."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a4",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Protection From Exploitation Of Vulnerabilities In Applications",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A4"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a4"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a4_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) ASLR and DEP/NX MUST be activated in the kernel and used by applications to make it harder\nto exploit vulnerabilities in applications. (2) Security functions of the kernel and of the standard\nlibraries (such as heap and stack protection) MUST NOT be disabled."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a5",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Secure Installation Of Software Packages",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A5"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a5"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a5_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) If software to be installed is to be compiled from source code, it MUST ONLY be unpacked,\nconfigured, and compiled using an unprivileged user account. (2) The software to be installed\nMUST NOT then be installed in the root file system of the server in question in an\nuncontrolled manner.\n\n(3) If the software is compiled from the source text, the selected parameters SHOULD be\ndocumented appropriately. (4) Based on this documentation, it SHOULD be possible to compile\nthe software in a transparent and reproducible manner at any time. (5) All further installation\nsteps SHOULD also be documented."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a6",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Managing Users And Groups",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A6"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a6"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a6_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) The corresponding management tools SHOULD be used for managing users and groups. (2) The\nconfiguration files /etc/passwd, /etc/shadow, /etc/group, and /etc/sudoers SHOULD NOT be\nedited directly."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a7",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Eliminated",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A7"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a7"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a7_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "This requirement has been eliminated."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a8",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Encrypted Access Via Secure Shell",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A8"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a8"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a8_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) Only Secure Shell (SSH) SHOULD be used to create an encrypted and authenticated interactive\nconnection between two IT systems. (2) All other protocols whose functions are covered by\nSecure Shell SHOULD be disabled completely. (3) For authentication, users SHOULD primarily\nuse certificates instead of passwords."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a9",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Eliminated",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A9"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a9"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a9_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "This requirement has been eliminated."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a10",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Preventing Further Intrusion When Vulnerabilities Are Exploited",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A10"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a10"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a10_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "(1) Services and applications SHOULD be protected with individual security architecture (e.g.\nwith AppArmor or SELinux). (2) In addition, chroot environments and LXC or Docker containers\nSHOULD be taken into account here. (3) It SHOULD be ensured that the standard profiles and\nrules provided are activated."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "sys-1.3.a11",
                    "class": "CAC_IMPORT",
                    "title": "Eliminated",
                    "props": [
                      {
                        "name": "label",
                        "value": "SYS.1.3.A11"
                      },
                      {
                        "name": "sort-id",
                        "value": "sys-01.03.a11"
                      }
                    ],
                    "parts": [
                      {
                        "id": "sys-1.3.a11_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "This requirement has been eliminated."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
